        "id": 1004035
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-07-14T11:40:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I did consider handling this in updatePhoneState, but as you mentioned it would be too late as the outgoing call would have been initiated and the audio routing would have been set up before invoking updatePhoneState. This could render the BluetoothHandsfree SCO state handling in a bad state. Therefore, the need to do this here. Please note that the terminateVirtualVoiceCall shall be a NOP if there is no active virtual-call and is hence harmless.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAA0n//+AA\u003d",
      "revId": "5220be0794449ba6f66cc1c813e72c6a75694f1d",
